1
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:40,760
Behind me is Brabourne School,

2
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:45,840
where news is just in that the missing
teenagers have been found after 18 days.

3
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:48,840
Now the waiting is finally over.

4
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:51,640
The four teenagers
attend Brabourne School,

5
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:53,960
where fees are in excess
of $30,000 a year.

6
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:57,440
Unconfirmed reports say
they have been taken to a local hospital,

7
00:03:57,480 --> 00:04:00,714
where their families
have been anxiously waiting.

8
00:04:05,320 --> 00:04:10,204
Michael Steel, son of rock guitarist
Stevie Steel, was one of the missing.

9
00:04:48,920 --> 00:04:50,800
Liz.

10
00:04:50,880 --> 00:04:53,080
–Liz!
–See you inside.

11
00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:54,200
He's going to kill us!

12
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:56,200
–No!
–Liz…

13
00:04:56,280 --> 00:04:59,480
–No! Stop!

14
00:05:08,040 --> 00:05:11,000
Hi. I'm Dr Horwood.
I'm here to help you.

15
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:18,520
Thanks.

16
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:59,920
Don't put me on Prozac or lithium.
I'm not crazy.

17
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:03,800
It's just my mum, she won't listen.

18
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:07,400
I'll listen.

19
00:06:10,760 --> 00:06:13,360
Do I have to talk about it today?

20
00:06:13,680 --> 00:06:16,280
You make it sound so terrible.

21
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:22,880
If you trust me and you work with me,

22
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:26,200
I really think I can help you feel better.

23
00:06:34,840 --> 00:06:38,880
So we do this at your speed, yeah?
We can stop at any time.

24
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:42,280
I won't lie to you:
this is going to be difficult,

25
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:46,320
but I know that you're brave enough
to get through it.

26
00:06:49,080 --> 00:06:51,200
Let's try a breathing exercise.

27
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:55,760
It might seem really… stupid,
but let's just give it a bash, OK?

28
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:58,800
Take a nice deep breath.

29
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:03,160
Feel your lungs fill up with air.
Good. Drop your shoulders.

30
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:07,040
And when you exhale,
tell all the muscles in your body to relax.

31
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:10,760
And whenever you feel ready,
just start to speak. OK?

32
00:07:33,360 --> 00:07:36,160
This is how it works at Brabourne.

33
00:07:36,640 --> 00:07:40,930
If you want to exist, you have
to be pretty. You have to be thin.

34
00:07:41,520 --> 00:07:44,080
Everyone else is wallpaper.

35
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:50,760
For years I was a nobody.

36
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:54,880
I watched the world from the edges
and learned not to dream.

37
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:57,440
–Oh, is he?

38
00:07:57,480 --> 00:08:00,120
My best friend, Martin, didn't care.

39
00:08:00,160 --> 00:08:03,040
His philosophy was:
“Take everything you can from them”.

40
00:08:03,080 --> 00:08:07,560
He said that their greed makes them
easy to control. It made him powerful.

41
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:09,640
But then the world changed.

42
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:13,080
Get ready, girls.
Mike Steel is single again.

43
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:16,240
Oh, my God!

44
00:08:21,840 --> 00:08:25,360
Mike Steel. American.
The son of a rock star.

45
00:08:25,440 --> 00:08:27,640
The missing part of my soul.

46
00:08:42,680 --> 00:08:45,560
–Get up!

47
00:08:46,920 --> 00:08:48,880
Please get up.

48
00:08:48,960 --> 00:08:52,240
Please, please be OK. Get up.

49
